Rana Daggubati is an Indian film actor and producer from Chennai, Tamil Nadu. He made his acting debut in 2010 with the Telugu film Leader, for which he won the Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut â€“ South. He has also acted in several other Telugu, Hindi and Tamil films. Rana comes from a prominent film family, as his grandfather, uncles and cousin are also actors. He has inherited a passion for cinema and has also worked as a film producer and in digital post-production.
